Kano State Government has constituted an eight–man Taskforce that will follow-up and collect accumulated Land Use Charges in the state.
The aim is to generate additional revenue needed to address development challenges, particularly, the provision of essential infrastructure and sustainable social services.
The Taskforce has Alhaji Habibu S. Mailemo, Special Adviser to the Governor on Revenue as Chairman. Other members are Ibrahim Ahmad Karaye, Special Adviser on Land Management, Director Government Business, Kano Internal Revenue Service, representative of Bureau for Land Management and representative of the Nigeria Police.
Other members include representative of the Director, Department of State Services; Representative of the Technical Adviser while Hafsat Wali, Deputy Director Legal, Bureau for Land Management will serve as Secretary.

